  "response": "Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev, commonly known as Sadhguru, is a well-known Indian yogi, mystic, and founder of the Isha Foundation, a non-profit organization offering yoga programs around the world. He has authored several books on spirituality, personal development, and well-being, and is a prominent speaker on various global platforms addressing topics like education, environment, and social issues.\n\nWhile Sadhguru has a large following and many supporters who appreciate his teachings and initiatives, like any public figure, he has also faced criticism and controversy from some individuals and groups. Allegations and accusations can arise for various reasons, and it's important to evaluate such claims critically by considering credible sources and evidence.\n\nIf you have specific concerns or questions about Sadhguru or his activities, I recommend researching reputable news outlets, official statements from the Isha Foundation, and other reliable sources to form a well-informed perspective.",
